Reasoning: The paper discusses the evaluation of deep neural networks, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The use of indices to evaluate the input data and data flowing through layers of a feedforward deep neural network suggests that the paper belongs to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the evaluation of dataflow in classification and regression problems, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV). The use of multi-layer neural networks also suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the evaluation of data separation and smoothness, which are concepts commonly used in data science (cs.DS).
